<subSubSection id="C32D63FDDE52FFECFF3FF0C1FAC04FCA" pageId="12" pageNumber="28" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B883076DE52FFECFF3FF0C1FEDD4EE5" blockId="12.[189,335,670,696]" box="[189,335,670,696]" pageId="12" pageNumber="28">
<heading id="D0C0871ADE52FFECFF3FF0C1FEDD4EE5" bold="true" box="[189,335,670,696]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="12" pageNumber="28" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B943EC64DE52FFECFF3FF0C1FEDD4EE5" bold="true" box="[189,335,670,696]" pageId="12" pageNumber="28">Description</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B883076DE52FFECFF3FF093FAC04FCA" blockId="12.[187,1398,716,919]" pageId="12" pageNumber="28">
Colony adnate, delicate, encrusting echinoid test. Autozooids arranged in uniserial chains with branching on both sides. New uniserial branches of autozooids starting from distolateral buds oriented at angle of 90° to the parent branch (
<figureCitation id="130C2CF3DE52FFECFD91F14CFDE64F70" box="[531,628,787,813]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[189,232,1928,1954]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,1440,1889]" captionTargetId="figure-214@11.[189,1398,1440,1889]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 7. Crepis gurjarensis Guha &amp; Gopikrishna, 2005 (GIS/B 0504). A. General view of the colony encrusting an echinoid test showing uniserial chains with branching on both sides. B. Close-up of an autozooid showing oval opesia, cryptocyst and well-developed gymnocyst." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6580798" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6580798/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="28">Fig. 7A</figureCitation>
). Autozooids elongate, pyriform. Opesia semioval with concave proximal edge, occupying roughly ⅓ of the frontal area. Cryptocyst well developed, smooth, descending into opesia. Marginal rim smooth, indistinct. Lateral walls smooth, irregular in basal contact. Gymnocyst smooth, tapering proximally, shrinks in proximal cauda (
<figureCitation id="130C2CF3DE52FFECFCD7F123FC204FCA" box="[853,946,892,919]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[189,232,1928,1954]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,1440,1889]" captionTargetId="figure-214@11.[189,1398,1440,1889]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 7. Crepis gurjarensis Guha &amp; Gopikrishna, 2005 (GIS/B 0504). A. General view of the colony encrusting an echinoid test showing uniserial chains with branching on both sides. B. Close-up of an autozooid showing oval opesia, cryptocyst and well-developed gymnocyst." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6580798" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6580798/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="28">Fig. 7B</figureCitation>
). Ancestrula and ooecium not seen.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C32D63FDDE52FFECFF3FF1E1FE924877" pageId="12" pageNumber="28" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B883076DE52FFECFF3FF1E1FEA24F85" blockId="12.[189,304,958,984]" box="[189,304,958,984]" pageId="12" pageNumber="28">
<heading id="D0C0871ADE52FFECFF3FF1E1FEA24F85" bold="true" box="[189,304,958,984]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="12" pageNumber="28" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B943EC64DE52FFECFF3FF1E1FEA24F85" bold="true" box="[189,304,958,984]" pageId="12" pageNumber="28">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B883076DE52FFECFF3FF1B3FE924877" blockId="12.[189,1398,1004,1066]" pageId="12" pageNumber="28">
The present species agrees with all the essential characters of 
<taxonomicName id="4C374BF5DE52FFECFC17F1B2FF694877" authority="Guha &amp; Gopikrishna, 2005" authorityName="Guha &amp; Gopikrishna" authorityYear="2005" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Crepis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="12" pageNumber="28" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="gurjarensis">
<emphasis id="B943EC64DE52FFECFC17F1B2FBE3485B" box="[917,1137,1005,1031]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="28">Crepis gurjarensis</emphasis>
Guha &amp; Gopikrishna, 2005
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
